  "prompt": "What are the hardest adjustments to make when visiting Georgia?",
  "response": "When visiting Georgia, some of the hardest adjustments might include:\n\n1. Language barrier\n- Georgian language is unique and difficult to understand\n- English is not widely spoken outside major cities\n\n2. Cultural differences\n- Complex social etiquette and customs\n- Different personal space norms\n- Strong emphasis on hospitality and traditional values\n\n3. Transportation challenges\n- Limited public transportation in rural areas\n- Unpredictable driving styles\n- Roads can be rough and mountainous\n\n4. Payment and infrastructure\n- Cash is still king in many places\n- Limited credit card acceptance\n- Potential inconsistent electricity and internet service\n\n5. Food and dining differences\n- Unique cuisine that might be unfamiliar\n- Long, social dining experiences\n- Different eating customs and expectations\n\n6. Time perception\n- More relaxed attitude toward time and scheduling\n- Less rigid punctuality compared to Western countries\n\n7. Climate variations\n- Significant temperature differences between regions\n- Mountain and coastal areas have very different weather patterns\n\n8. Bureaucratic processes\n- Complex administrative procedures\n- Potential challenges with visas and documentation\n\nThese adjustments can vary depending on individual experiences and specific regions within Georgia.",
